## Architecture Pattern

### MVC (Model-View-Controller)

Strictly follow Rails MVC pattern:

**Models:**
- Business logic
- Validations
- Associations
- Scopes
- Database interactions

**Views:**
- Presentation layer only
- ERB templates
- Partials for reusability
- No business logic

**Controllers:**
- Coordinate between models and views
- Handle HTTP requests
- Thin controllers (<10 lines per action)
- Maximum 2 instance variables per action